This empty file disables Jekyll on GitHub Pages, and it is load-bearing.

Jekyll silently drops paths beginning with a dot, so without this file
.well-known/apple-app-site-association is never published and every
universal link falls back to Safari. The failure is invisible: the build
succeeds, the site works, and only the AASA is missing.

Do not delete it. Jekyll is not otherwise used here; every file in this
directory is served verbatim.
